cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.PF

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with clock synchronization across wireless networks. Additionally, the paper discusses the performance analysis of cooperative network synchronization, which could also fall under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of closed-form asymptotic expressions to derive performance limits suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory). The concepts of random walk and network topology could place the paper under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper's focus on performance and efficiency could also make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.PF (Performance).
